Description: Pottery vase made of rough straw tempered Nile silt, with rounded body, short neck and rolled over lip. Body deformed on one side.
Curator's comments: Probably E. R. Ayrton & W. L. S. Loat, Pre-dynastic cemetery at El Mahasna (London, 1911), pl. xxxiv 62a, which is illustrated as Rough ware R62C in Petrie’s Corpus of Prehistoric Pottery.
